docs.lead_paragraph: What a miserable month of May ! Usually, we have here, at this season, pleasant gatherings on the green sward, under the shade of forest trees, with a profusion of ripe strawberries, and such excellent cream as is supplied by the metropolitan milk maids, who bring it to our doors in the veritable milk pails. But this year a crevasse seems to have been opened overhead. and a sunshine is a most desirable novelty.

docs.lead_paragraph: Our dispatches from Washington this morning relative to the exciting topic of the day will be found highly interesting and important. Lord NAPIER, it is stated positively, has forwarded instructions to the Commander-in-Chief of the British naval forces on the West India station that the visitations of American vessels must be discontinued.
